    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1546"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1546">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/357.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary to the President</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: For your information I send you a
                    copy of the dispatch which the President this afternoon sent to Colonel
                    Goethals.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles D. Hilles.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to Colonel
                                <persName type="to">Goethals</persName>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-23">
                                <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1912</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>I wish you would communicate confidentially and discreetly to Federico Boyd
                        that we of the American Government hope that when President Arosemena leaves
                        he will remain to take his place by virtue of his present office as <hi
                            rend="italic">secundo designato</hi> during the six months prior to
                        election. Impress on him that we think that his exercise of the office is
                        needed to steady matters in the Republic and that if he abandons the
                        government at this time it will bring about a situation not favorable to the
                        future prosperity of Panama.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
